        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 6:23PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 622 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Saragosa, or 28 miles southeast of Toyah, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Balmorhea, Balmorhea Lake, Saragosa, and Verhalen.

This includes Interstate 10 between mile markers 205 and 235.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
